const headHtml = "<title>Your First 50M Coins in Hypixel SkyBlock</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"A progression-first guide to your first 50M coins in Hypixel SkyBlock, built around stable flips, farming, mining and capital discipline rather than one giant lucky score.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/first-50m-coins-guide\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/first-50m-coins-guide\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Your First 50M Coins in Hypixel SkyBlock\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Build the first 50M coins through layered reliable methods instead of chasing one oversized flip or impossible drop.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\n        \"headline\": \"Your First 50M Coins in Hypixel SkyBlock\",\n        \"description\": \"Progression-first guide to earning the first 50M coins in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\n        \"datePublished\": \"2026-05-25\",\n        \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-18\",\n        \"author\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"NotEnoughCoins\"\n        },\n        \"publisher\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"Coflnet GmbH\"\n        },\n        \"url\": \"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/first-50m-coins-guide\"\n      }\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-05-25 • Progression</a>\n          <h1>Your First 50M Coins in Hypixel SkyBlock</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">The first 50 million coins is where many SkyBlock players either stabilize or spiral. Stable players treat the milestone as a progression problem: layer dependable income streams, preserve capital and upgrade into better methods deliberately. Unstable players treat it like a lottery ticket problem: one giant flip, one improbable drop, one expensive gamble. The safest way to reach 50M is boring in the best possible way.</p>\n\n          <div class=\"note\">\n            <strong>Research basis:</strong> The full guide series, especially creator advice that favors layered progress, capital discipline and controlled upgrades over jackpot chasing.\n          </div>\n\n          <h2>Start with income you can explain</h2>\n          <p>The safest route to the first 50M begins with methods you understand clearly. Small AH flips, passive bazaar orders, NPC-to-bazaar routes, early Garden progress and simple craft work all teach the same skill: why the money appeared. That clarity matters because it keeps you steady when a session looks weaker than the highlight clips on YouTube.</p>\n          <p>Once you understand the reason behind the profit, you stop panicking during slower hours and you stop abandoning solid routes every time someone posts a bigger screenshot.</p>\n\n          <h2>Layer methods instead of replacing them too early</h2>\n          <p>Healthy SkyBlock progression is usually additive. A player might begin with cheap flipping, add passive bazaar work, then build farming or mining once the account and bankroll justify it. That layering creates resilience. If one market cools off, the whole income plan does not collapse.</p>\n          <p>By contrast, players who jump fully into one expensive strategy too early often become fragile. One bad purchase or weak day can knock them backward. The first 50M usually comes from stacking several decent methods, not from discovering one perfect one.</p>\n\n          <h2>Upgrade on evidence, not emotion</h2>\n          <p>Every time you want to pivot methods, ask the same question: what evidence says the next route is ready? Do you have the capital, the knowledge, the account progression and the time to execute it correctly? If not, the smart move is often to keep compounding where you already have an edge.</p>\n          <p>Use live tools to support those transitions. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl flipper</a> is useful for free modifier-aware AH context, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/flips\">Skyblock.bz flips</a> helps compare current opportunities by ROI, and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/smart\">BazaarTracker smart</a> plus <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">demand</a> help check whether bazaar-side routes are ready for more size. The tools do not replace progression logic. They help confirm it.</p>\n\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/ah-flipping-guide-2026\">Auction House Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/farming-progression-guide-2026\">Farming Progression Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/mining-money-making-guide-2026\">Best Mining Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best paired tools</h3>\n            <ul class=\"tool-list\">\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl flipper</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flips\">SkyCofl flips hub</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/flips\">Skyblock.bz flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features\">BazaarPro features</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/smart\">BazaarTracker smart</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/demand\">BazaarTracker demand</a></li>\n            </ul>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best for</h3>\n            <p>Early and midgame players who want a realistic path to the first serious bankroll without relying on one lucky event.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Method</h3>\n            <p>This page ties the full guide series back into one progression framework so readers can choose the next sensible method for their current stage.</p>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
